    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="KR2o0001-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-h.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T22:02:47.333+09:00">3. Doubting the Ancients</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:12:57.557+09:00">The tasks of the historians in antiquity</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:02:18.848+09:00">were divided in two:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:04:24.17+09:00">one was to record the words (that were spoken)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:10:07.419+09:00">the other was to record the actions.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:13:46.43+09:00">However, the learning of the scholars of antiquity </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:24:04.718+09:00">was focused on the words.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T19:19:40.247+09:00">For example: of the rules of Yu and Xia,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:51:05.093+09:00">the decrees of the Shang and Zhou,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:51:20.827+09:00">the words of Zhong Hui and Zhou Ren</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T18:53:23.996+09:00">and the discourses of Shi Yi and Zang Wen</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T19:38:19.373+09:00">all the speeches of wandering orators, responses of foreign envoys, advice or written suggestions to a ruler,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T19:41:43.443+09:00">there is none that is not quoted</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T19:41:50.202+09:00">or returned to as a model.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T19:43:17.516+09:00">For the (records of) actions, things did not go that way.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T20:06:59.249+09:00">Shao Hao named his officials after birds,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T20:07:32.521+09:00">Yao Tang tamed dragons in order to be appointed to an official position,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T22:49:16.248+09:00">When the Xia went into temporary decline,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T22:52:36.737+09:00">Hou Xi and Han Zhao were among the villains (responsable).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T22:50:43.319+09:00">When the state of Qi was first established,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-25T23:25:33.209+09:00">(making for) unheard-of (events) and remarkable actions.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-25T23:33:53.529+09:00">(the clans of) Pugu and Boling were among its rulers.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-20T23:10:39.444+09:00">All of these founded states or supported their dynasty,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-25T23:36:48.249+09:00">The scholars of later generations, however,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-25T23:39:50.427+09:00">only rarely transmitted any explanations about them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T17:18:03.642+09:00">whereas the documents recording words were viewed as important.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T17:18:19.737+09:00">This goes to show that the works of history that recorded the actions did not circulate (widely)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T17:18:43.96+09:00">may perhaps have some coarse knowledge about small aspects of them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-1a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T17:19:53.911+09:00">Only a gentleman of vast learning</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-2a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T18:47:41.223+09:00">As for the tradition of Zuo (Qiuming; i.e., the "Chunqiu Zuozhuan"),</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T18:47:48.547+09:00">although the exegesis is basically conform to the classic (the "Chunqiu"),</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T18:08:24.287+09:00">he (also) talks about various other things.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T18:48:41.242+09:00">Therefore, the Confucians of the Han dynasty</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T18:14:40.945+09:00">resented it intensely.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T18:48:02.489+09:00">Thus, the (other) two traditions (i.e., "Gongyang zhuan" und "Guliang zhuan") circulated widely</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T22:09:53.62+09:00">and were the only ones to gain renown in the course of time.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T18:31:12.171+09:00">Among the writings of Confucius and his disciples,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T18:47:25.873+09:00">the "Lunyu" only transmits words and remarks,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T18:47:32.454+09:00">while the "Kongzi jiayu" also reports actions and deeds.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T19:35:35.036+09:00">simply calling them "Lunyu".</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T19:35:29.731+09:00">Since antiquity, however, scholars and followers have handed them (these texts) down,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T19:35:49.132+09:00">This demonstrates</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T22:08:31.07+09:00">that it is clearly the result of the ancient's constantly making light of (records of) actions and taking words seriously.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T19:36:09.769+09:00">Nevertheless, starting from Yao of Tang and</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T19:36:16.873+09:00">ending with Mu of Qin,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T19:36:24.072+09:00">there are only a hundred chapters of records about them in the "Shangshu".</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T19:36:35.069+09:00">And that which the "Shangshu" transmits</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T19:36:48.392+09:00">is largely based on words.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T19:47:22.926+09:00">When it comes to rise and fall (of states etc.) and to actions and deeds,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T19:47:57.087+09:00">it (the "Shangshu") does not even record one.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T19:54:08.802+09:00">I could still say a lot about the omissions (of the "Shangshu")!</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-4a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T20:01:57.375+09:00">It is stated in the "Lunyu":</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-4a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T19:59:34.023+09:00">"The gentleman works to perfect what is splendid in others,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-4a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T20:00:17.228+09:00">and he does not work to perfect what is ugly in others."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-4a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T20:02:05.291+09:00">It is also said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-4a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T20:03:09.436+09:00">"Matters that are completed one does not explain,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-4a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T20:06:23.474+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-4a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T20:06:15.037+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-4a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T20:06:18.969+09:00">what is past one does not censure."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-4a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T20:06:43.706+09:00">matters that have gone their proper course one does not remonstrate on,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-4a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T20:07:11.191+09:00">It is also said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-4a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T21:31:44.37+09:00">"The common people may be made to follow one,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-4a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T21:32:09.76+09:00">they cannot be made to understand one."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T21:36:12.19+09:00">Therefore, the people that came after learned about the words,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T21:37:37.325+09:00">(but) the actions of the emperors and kings of Tang, Yu and the states that came thereafter</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-3a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T21:39:19.959+09:00">have not yet become known.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T21:44:20.153+09:00">Those were the words of Confucius when he established his teachings.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T22:13:03.341+09:00">With regard to works of historiography</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T22:13:13.295+09:00">his opinion was the same.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:53:43.947+09:00">Thus (in a sweeping way), he called good what was good on the basis of its goodness, </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T22:44:53.406+09:00">and, even if it had bad aspects,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:56:04.25+09:00">did not criticise it any more;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T22:45:15.642+09:00">and he called bad what was bad on the basis of its badness, </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-04-27T22:45:24.164+09:00">and, even if it had good aspects,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:56:23.34+09:00">should not be praised any more.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:48:13.305+09:00">This (however) is why Mengzi states:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T22:50:52.267+09:00">(just as) Jie and Zhou were not completely bad."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T22:51:02.104+09:00">"Yao and Shun were not completely good </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T22:59:43.466+09:00">Wei Wendi said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:33:38.255+09:00">"I know about the precedents of Yao and Shun."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T22:59:34.568+09:00">Han Jingdi said:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-03T06:26:32.655+09:00">"It is not stupid that the scholars in their discussions don't talk about</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:02:42.035+09:00">how Tang and Wu received the Heavenly Mandate."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:50:15.031+09:00">All these also show that the worthies of former times also looked closely (at their sources)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:14:59.38+09:00">and already had a preliminary understanding (of it).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.36" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:40:46.647+09:00">Although their mouths could not express it,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:51:45.088+09:00">they knew in their heart which (parts) were not right.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:52:03.654+09:00">Of these cases, there turned out to be a lot.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:51:31.145+09:00">However, they were (also) constrained by rites and law</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-5a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-02T23:51:37.037+09:00">and these limitations were applied to teaching and instruction.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-6a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-03T00:13:37.305+09:00">Then, as regards the historiographical work of Lu, the Chunqiu:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-6a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-03T00:13:44.31+09:00">For the sake of (protecting the image of) the worthies on the outside</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-6a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-03T00:13:45.781+09:00">and for the sake of the inside (stability) of the state itself,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-6a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-03T00:20:30.461+09:00">the precedents were twisted and rougly woven,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-6a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-03T00:21:04.656+09:00">and all the actions were concealed or avoided as taboo.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T17:20:19.715+09:00">This (which was included in the Chunqiu) then were the authoritative words of the Duke of Zhou.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:36:49.061+09:00">This being so, what need is there for the "Chunqiu",</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T17:23:36.829+09:00">that is not (already) covered by the Six Classics?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T17:25:29.811+09:00">They are all like this.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T17:33:04.881+09:00">Thus, when we examine how Confucius revised the "Shangshu",</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T17:47:21.992+09:00">(we see that) Jie of the Xia criticised Tang (of the Shang)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T17:53:05.56+09:00">and that the King of Wu beheaded Zhou (of the Shang).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:14:58.209+09:00">These precedents are very clear,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:17:09.69+09:00">and (they show that those who commit) butchery don't last.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:17:28.659+09:00">(Note:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:18:19.28+09:00">These events are from the "Documents of Zhou".</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:28:43.474+09:00">The "Documents of the Zou" are the remainder of those of the "Shangshu" that Confucius eliminated (when he was supposedly compiling the "Shangshu").)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:36:50.432+09:00">When we examine how Confucius established the Rites (in the "Chunqiu"),</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:38:59.152+09:00">(we see that) grief and sadness are not destined to be</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:46:55.507+09:00">and (that) evilness and ??? do not end;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:48:08.519+09:00">however (the Chunqiu), with a boastful brush and splendid words,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:50:00.373+09:00">states that "in Lu, there is no usurpation or killing of rulers."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:59:00.182+09:00">When we examine the "Shijing" as revised by Confucius,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:57:00.894+09:00">(we see that) all the (songs of) "Guo Feng"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2o0001_tls_039-7a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#Lea.Wallraff" modified="2022-05-04T18:58:21.98+09:00">contain criticism and reprimands</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
